EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to crimes; prohibiting certain persons from
selling, offering for sale or purchasing child remains;
providing a penalty; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates various crimes against public decency and good morals
2 and provides penalties to be imposed upon persons who commit such crimes.
3 (Chapter 201 of NRS) This bill: (1) prohibits a person from selling, offering for sale
4 or purchasing child remains except under certain circumstances; and (2) provides
5 that a person who violates this prohibition is guilty of a misdemeanor.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 201 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, a person shall
4 not sell, offer for sale or purchase child remains.
5 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to the sale or
6 purchase of child remains by a hospital, accredited medical
7 school, dental school or institution of higher education if the sale
8 or purchase is related to education, research or a similar purpose.
9 3. A person who violates the provisions of subsection 1 is
10 guilty of a misdemeanor.
