1 4. As used in this section:
2 (a) “Child” means a person who is less than 18 years of age.
3 (b) “Child remains” means the body of a deceased child, or
4 part of the body which has been removed from a living child, in
5 any stage of decomposition.
6 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
